write code in Typescript
rewrite any code in JavaScript into Typescript
when adding environment variables, don't edit .env file. edit .env.example file instead. provide description for each environment variable and how to set it.
always use context7 mcp server for current documentation of the tech stack you are currently working on.
always use sequential-thinking mcp for thinking on the implementation
when designing or adding new code, always consider YAGNI + SOLID + KISS + DRY principles
after editing a .ts, .tsx, .js or .jsx file, check if it is over 500 lines. if yes, please split it down into separate files without breaking any functionalities
when you find an error, find and fix all possible root causes of that error. use context7 mcp server to search the current documentation about the error
only make changes you are at least 95% confident in
when you are not sure about something, use context7 mcp to get the best practice on solving your problem
when running server test, use vitest.server.config.ts
when running client test, use vitest.optimized.config.ts
when running test, use the commands specified in the root package.json